<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal Ousts 10-man Turkey 2-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Portugal captured the first
semifinals place at the Euro 2000 when they beat 10-men Turkey 2-0
in Saturday's quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
The victory was the first one in any major event since 1984 for
Portugal, who dominated the match at the Amsterdam ArenA and had
all the two goals scored by Benfica striker Nuno Gomes.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese will meet the winner of the France-Spain quarter-
final, which to be played on Sunday, in the semifinals in Brussels
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nuno Gomes opened the scores for Portugal at the 44th minute
and added the second at 56. The two goals gave the Portuguese,
known as 'the Brazilians of Europe' in full domination after
Turkey defender Alpay Ozalan was sent off in the 29th minute of a
scrappy and ill-disciplined first half.
</P>
<P>
Alpay was dismissed for retaliation after he had jumped into a
challenge with Fernando Couto, the Turk lashing out with his arm
as Couto lay on the pitch, but some saw the decision as harsh.
</P>
<P>
The Turks also missed a penalty shortly before the interval,
when Arif Erdem fired his spot-kick straight at Vitor Baia, after
being adjudged to have been brought down by Couto. The goalkeeper
then blocked the follow-up shot from Hakan Sukur.
</P>
<P>
The opening period began with Portugal, producing bursts of
their delightful one-touch flowing football, on top, but soon
degenerated into a series of fouls which resulted in five yellow
cards and one red one in 12 minutes. The final tally was seven
yellows.
</P>
<P>
The second came after a sweeping and skilful move, started on
the left by Dimas, who found Figo.
</P>
<P>
The Barcelona forward outwitted Hakan Unsul comprehensively and,
after a burst of speed, pulled the ball back across goal for Nuno
Gomes to glide it home from close range.
</P>
</TEXT>
