<HEADLINE> 1st Lead: Seven Bomb Blasts hit Southern Philippine city </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Seven bomb explosions rocked the
southern Philippine city of General Santos on Saturday evening,
killing one woman and injuring 36 others, according to a TV report
here.
</P>
<P>
The woman, identified as Elena Kabasag, died on arrival upon
being brought to the general hospital in the city, said the ABS-
CBN News Channel report.
</P>
<P>
A wounded five-year-old boy is now in critical condition, it
added
</P>
<P>
The series of bombings began around 18:30 local time (10:30 GMT)
with minutes apart between each blast.
</P>
<P>
Police has sealed off entries and exits of the city.
</P>
<P>
So far, no individual or group has claimed responsibility for
the bombings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
