<HEADLINE> Semifinals Postponed by Rain at Den Bosch Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The men's semifinals at the Den
Bosch Open in the Netherlands were halted during the first set on
Saturday and postponed until Sunday because of rain.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Patrick Rafter of Australia was 5-2 ahead of
unseeded Martin Damm of the Czech Republic when play was stopped.
</P>
<P>
The match between Fifth seed Michael Chang of the U.S. and
second seed Nicolas Escude of France stood at 2-2.
</P>
<P>
The semifinals will resume on Sunday at 10:00 a.m. (0800 GMT)
followed by the final at about 1:00 p.m. (1100 GMT), organizers
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
