<HEADLINE> Syrian Parliament Special Committee Supports Bashar's Candidacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A special committee of Syrian
parliament on Sunday gave its blessings to the nomination of Bashar
al-Assad for the post of president to succeed his late father,
President Hafez al-Assad, who died on June 10.
</P>
<P>
According to the official SANA news agency, the 70-member
committee of the 250-seat People's Assembly discussed the
nomination of Bashar by the ruling Baath party and expressed its "
total support" for his candidacy for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
A full session of the parliament is expected to be held Monday
to approve Bashar's nomination and set a date for a referendum for
the country's nearly 7 million voters to decide whether Bashar will
be the new ruler.
</P>
<P>
If approved, Bashar will serve as Syria's 16th president for a
seven-year term. He has already been appointed supreme commander of
the armed forces and was elected secretary of the Baath party's top
policy-making body at the end of the party's ninth conference last
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
