<HEADLINE> Iranian President Highlights Pyongyang-Seoul Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
on Sunday sent separate messages to leaders of South Korea and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to congratulate them
on their landmark summit earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
In his message to South Korean President Kim Dae-jung, Khatami
said the success of the two leaders' summit demonstrated their
determination to end the division of the Korean Peninsula and to
bring peace and stability there, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Also in his message to DPRK leader Kim Jong-il, Khatami called
the initiative of the two leaders to break the ground for dialog
as "a brave decision" to strengthen peace and stability in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Khatami observed in the messages that the summit was a turning
point in the history of the nation of Korea, adding the success of
the meeting was an important step in materializing the long-held
aspirations of the South Korean and DPRK people for peace and co-
existence. 
</P>
