<HEADLINE> Britain Charges Three Dutchmen Over Drug Seizure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- British officials said on Sunday
that three Dutchmen have been charged with drug smuggling after
the seizure of eight tons of cannabis from a yacht off the
Scottish coast.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Britain's Customs and Excise Department said
the three Dutchmen would appear at a Court in Aberdeen, the North-
east port city of Britain, on Monday, charged in connection with
the illegal importation of a controlled substance.
</P>
<P>
British customs officers boarded the yacht "Red Scorpion" on
Saturday while it was in international waters off the northeast
coast of Scotland.
</P>
<P>
They took charge of the yacht after discovering the cannabis
resin, estimated to be worth over 20 million pounds (about 30
million United States dollars).
</P>
<P>
"Smugglers being smugglers, they will make diversions to get
into any point of the United Kingdom mainland," the spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
