<HEADLINE> Egyptian, Israeli Presidents Praise Bashar as "Kind Man" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and
his Israeli counterpart said on Sunday that Bashar al-Assad, son of
late Syrian President Hafez al-Assad, is "a kind man" and would be
a good president of Syria.
</P>
<P>
Bashar, a young eye doctor who did not come from the military
but looked after patients, "must be a kind man," Weizman said after
meeting with Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
"Bashar al-Assad will be an excellent president," Mubarak said
at a press conference held jointly with Weizman.
</P>
<P>
Hafez al-Assad died on June 10. The Syrian leadership has since
been taking steps to promote Bashar, the heir apparent, to Syria's
top position.
</P>
<P>
"Everything reported on the frailness of the Syrian leadership
are mere false rumors," Mubarak stressed, saying that the Syrian
leadership will continue and Bashar will be "persistent and firm."
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Weizman left Cairo for home, ending a short "
farewell" visit to Egypt. He is due to retire from politics early
July, three years before his term ends, partly for allegations of
corruption and tax fraud.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak and Weizman, both former pilots who fought in the wars
between the two countries, have known each other since Egypt and
Israel made peace in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Weizman was one of the key figures who played a benevolent role
in making peace between Egypt and Israel, Mubarak said.
</P>
<P>
He paid tribute to the efforts Weizman has exerted and continues
to exert as president for a comprehensive peace in the Middle East.
</P>
</TEXT>
