<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for International Relief to Drought-hit Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi on Sunday called on the international community to
rush help to counter the famine and drought crisis in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The need for a firm decision in this regard is now felt more
than ever before and all world countries are required to prevent a
human tragedy in the region, Asefi said here.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the severe famine and drought disaster in most
parts of Afghanistan, he underlined the need to dispatch relief aid
for the deprived and oppressed people in the country.
</P>
<P>
Under present circumstances, the dispatch of international
relief aid seems to be vital, Asefi said, adding that the aid will
help prevent Afghan refugees from entering Iran, Afghanistan's
western neighbor.
</P>
<P>
Iran has taken in more than 1.5 million Afghan refugees over the
past two decades, and an influx of more refugees will worsen the
situation, the spokesman pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He also urged all Afghan factions to respond positively to calls
of neighboring countries, the Organization of Islamic Conference
and the international community to restore peace and stability in
their country.
</P>
<P>
Afghan political groups should set up a broad-based government
and avoid any military operation which will surely aggravate the
present situation, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
