<HEADLINE> Chirac Begins State Visit to Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, June 25 (Xinhua)--French President Jacques Chirac
arrived in Hanover Sunday afternoon, beginning his three-day state
visit to Germany.
</P>
<P>
A week before France to take over the rotating presidency of
the European Union (EU), Chirac's visit is expected to focus on
the future of the EU, including its structural reform, economic
policy, its enlargement, common foreign policy, and common defense.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder met Chirac at the
guesthouse of Lower Saxonia state in Hanover. The two were due to
jointly accept an interview of German ZDF television Sunday
evening over German-Franco relation and the EU policy.
</P>
<P>
The official schedule of Chirac will begin on Monday, when
German President Johannes Rau is due to host a ceremony to greet
Chirac in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
The visit will be highlightened on Tuesday, when Chirac is due
to give a speech in German parliament, the Bundestag. Chirac is
the first foreign state head invited to give speech in the
Reichstag building.
</P>
<P>
Berlin cabinet expected closer cooperation between Germany and
France, especially in the EU enlargement and common defense.
</P>
</TEXT>
