<HEADLINE> China-Aided NAM Convention Center to Be Completed on Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus
Samad Azad was informed Sunday that the construction of the
Bangabandhu International Convention Center (BICC) would be
completed by August next year, at least one month ahead of the
tentative schedule of the Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) summit.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Chinese Ambassador to Bangladesh Wang Chungui,
the foreign minister visited the BICC under construction and
expressed satisfaction over the progress of the construction work.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project will be 2 billion taka (40
million U.S. dollars), of which the Chinese government will
provide 27 million dollars in grant and interest-free loan.
</P>
<P>
The construction work of the BICC for holding the 13th NAM
summit next year was entrusted to Shanghai Construction Group
under an agreement signed in February. About 90 Chinese engineers
and technicians have been working day and night since then.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister extended his sincere thanks and gratitude
to the government and great people of China for their all-out
assistance and technical support for the construction of the BICC.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Wang Chungui said that the BICC would be yet
another symbol of friendship between the peoples of China and
Bangladesh. Bangladesh would be able to utilize the center for
holding international meetings and conferences, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
