<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 39 Nepalese Killed Due to Floods and Landslides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A total of 39 Nepalese have been
killed so far due to floods and landslides caused by incessant
rains that began in mid-June, said Home Minister Govinda Joshi
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Joshi told the parliament in a statement of public importance
that about 22 persons were injured by floods, two were missing and
hundreds of families were affected.
</P>
<P>
The total damage caused by floods and landslides has amounted
to about 20 million rupees (300,000 U.S. dollars) and districts in
western, mid-western and far-western districts were most affected,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Joshi said the Nepali government has taken measures for rescue
and relief and 4.2 million rupees (60,000 U.S. dollars) has been
released for the affected families and areas.
</P>
<P>
During the monsoon season that lasts from mid-June to September
every year, Nepal is hit by floods and landslides that claim
hundreds of lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
