<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Beat Chongqing to Keep Leading Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- League leaders Dalian Shide
consolidated their leading status in the Chinese first division
soccer league after beating the visiting Chongqing Longxin 2-0 in
the 15th round on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese international Sun Jihai shook off several defenders to
score in the box with eight minutes into action, giving Shide a 1-
0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Adilsondos Santos made it 2-0 in the 51st minute on a
corner kick. Longxin's best chance came in the injury time but a
powerful shot hit the bar.
</P>
<P>
"It's a difficult match for both sides in Dalian's steaming
heat, fortunately we finally won it," said Dalian's Yugoslav head
coach Milorad Kosanovic.
</P>
<P>
He added: "In the last nine matches, our players have shown
their increasingly good form."
</P>
<P>
Dalian, four-time league champions in six seasons, have kept
unbeaten in the last nine rounds, winning seven and tying two and
standing atop in the tally with 33 points.
</P>
<P>
Longxin now stay in the fifth place by collecting 26 points
with 7-5-3.
</P>
<P>
China's national team head coach Bora Milutinovic, who returned
from the Euro 2000 yesterday, made a special travel from Beijing
to Dalian to watch the match.
</P>
<P>
"It's a fantastic match," the Yugoslav legendary coach said. "
Dalian played much better than Longxin."
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua, the 1997 league champion, beat Jilin Aodong 2-
1 to remain second placer in the standings with 30 points,
followed by defending champion Luneng Taishan with 29, who
defeated Xiamen Xiaxin 2-0.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Shenzhen Ping'an routed Yunnan Hongta 2-0,
Shenyang Haishi ousted Liaoning Fushun 2-0, Qingdao Hainiu edged
Sichuan Quanxing 1-0 and Beijing Guo'an beat Tianjin Taida 2-1.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
