<HEADLINE> Drug Hotline Opens in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 25 (Xinhua) -- People in central China's Henan
Province can now dial a hotline for information on dangers of
drugs and national and local laws against drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
The 24/7 service, available at #16800626, provides professional
advice on drug abstinence, and brief explanations of local drug
addiction treatment centers.
</P>
<P>
The effort is to publicize the basics on drug awareness and to
encourage citizens to help police uncover drug trafficking and
related crimes.
</P>
<P>
In another development, over 10,000 teenagers in northeastern
China's Jilin Province today signed their names on two white
banners, vowing to stay drug-free and to fight drug-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations set June 26 as the International Day Against
Drug Abuse in 1987, with the support of 138 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
