<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Denmark Gives Grant to Bangladesh for Agriculture Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive 486 million
Danish kroner (72 million U.S. dollars) as grant from Denmark for
its Agriculture Sector Program Support, an External Resources
Division (ERD) press release said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
An umbrella agreement to this effect was signed at the ERD
today between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be used for implementation of the four
components of the Agriculture Sector Program Support in Bangladesh,
which comprise crop production, aquaculture, livestock development
and institutional support.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the program is to improve living conditions
through optimized, integrated and sustainable agricultural
production.
</P>
<P>
For each of the components, separate agreement will be signed
under the umbrella agreement, the press release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
