<HEADLINE> Rafter Wins Third Title at Den Bosch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Patrick
Rafter of Australia took only 57 minutes to beat second seed
Nicolas Escude 6-1, 6-3 and win his third consecutive Den Bosch
title on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded Rafter took the first set in 23 minutes,
breaking Escude three times and dropping only one point on his own
service.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, who seemed to have fully recovered from a long-standing
shoulder injury, had to fight off one breakpoint to finally take
the second set 6-3 in 34 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Rafter beat Czech Martin Damm 6-2, 6-1 while Escude defeated
fifth-seeded American Michael Chang 7-6, 6-2 in the semifinals
earlier on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
