<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wuhan Air Crash Investigation Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The cockpit voice recorder recovered
from the Yun-7 plane which crashed in Wuhan last Thursday has been
sent to the General Administration of Civil Aviation of China to
help investigators determine the cause of the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Initial study of the wreckage has ruled out sabotage, and no
evidence of an explosion has been found, investigation officials
said.
</P>
<P>
All 42 crew members and passengers aboard the Yun-7 plane were
killed when it crashed on the afternoon of June 22 in central
China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Thick clouds surrounded Hubei's Tianhe Airport when the plane
took off that day, and storms accompanied by lightning and hail
hit the area, reports show.
</P>
<P>
None of the crew members on board reportedly had consumed
alcohol in the eight hours prior to takeoff, investigators have
learned.
</P>
<P>
The city government of Wuhan set up a special task force made
up of members from the local public security, health and civil
affairs departments to handle post-crash trauma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rescuers Recover More Bodies from Capsized Boat in SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Rescuers today recovered 45 more
bodies who perished after their overloaded boat capsized last
Thursday on the upper reaches of China's Yangtze River, bringing
the death toll to 62.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said 70 people are still missing.
</P>
<P>
Today, 11 rescue teams, 11 boats and over 200 people were
searching along the river near Hejiang, southwestern Sichuan
Province, for survivors and bodies.
</P>
<P>
The passenger vessel Rong Jian, which had a maximum holding
capacity of 101 people, was carrying 221 passengers when it hit a
rock and sank while sailing in foggy conditions on June 22.
</P>
<P>
Overloading and the captain's malpractice have been named as
the causes of the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Three people, including the ship's owner Liang Rubing, and its
captain Zhou Shoujin, have been detained by local police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
