<HEADLINE> DRC Allies' Summit Begins in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The one-day heads of state summit
to discuss ways of speeding up the implementation of the peace
agreement in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) started in
Zimbabwean capital Harare on Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The summit, also expected to discuss the ceasefire violations
by Ugandan and Rwandan forces in Kisangani, is being attended by
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, DRC President Laurent Kabila
and Namibian President Sam Nujoma.
</P>
<P>
Angolan President Eduardo dos Santos could not attend because
of political problems in his country.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda and Uganda are backing rival rebel groups trying to
topple the DRC government led by Kabila who is being supported by
troops from Zimbabwe, Angola and Namibia. 
</P>
