proposal for Medicare drug benefits, making it more generous to
millions of elderly people and more costly to the federal
government. The plan would cost 79 billion dollars over five
years, or more than twice as much as the 38 billion dollars
proposal he sent Congress as part of his budget request in
February.
</P>
<P>
-- Zimbabwe held long-awaited national elections. Despite
weeks of political unrest, early voting was reported free of the
brazen intimidation that marked the campaign. 
