<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Stresses Party's Role in SOEs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
today emphasized the importance of Communist Party building work
in State-owned enterprises (SOEs), which are urged to reform
themselves and end loss-making.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged Party members in SOEs at a meeting here today to study
President Jiang Zemin's instruction on the Party's role. Jiang's
instruction says that the Communist Party represents the
development requirements of China's advanced social productive
forces, the progressive course of China's advanced culture, and
the fundamental interests of the overwhelming majority of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He asked officials in SOEs to use the instruction as an
ideological weapon in advancing SOE reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Party should strengthen its leadership in SOEs, Wu said. He
also urged SOEs to accelerate technological upgrading, and enhance
their internal management to improve efficiency. He also stressed
the importance of the social security system, saying that social
protection should be improved to ensure the stability of
enterprises and the society at large.  
</P>
</TEXT>
