<HEADLINE> No New U.S. Proposals on Mideast Peace: Senior Palestinian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Envoy to the Middle East Denis
Ross has not conveyed any new U.S. proposals during his Mideast
trip, said Chief palestinian Negotiator Saeb Erekat.
</P>
<P>
In remarks to Voice of Palestine radio on Sunday, Erekat said, "
Ross has not any proposals in his current trip neither on the
transitional nor on the final talks" between the Palestinians and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
"Ross told us that he would listen to the view points of both
sides then forward the attitudes to the U.S. administration after
he meets with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on Sunday", he
added.
</P>
<P>
The palestinian official stressed that U.S. administration" has
to find mechanisms to carry out the agreed third phase Israeli
troops redeployment by August 7."
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Palestinians said they had accepted a U.S. proposal
that postponing the third phase troop deployment, overdue on June
23, for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Erekat pointed out that he handed Ross a list of should-be-
released Palestinian prisoners in Israel jails under Sharm al-
Sheikh interim deal signed last September.
</P>
<P>
On the Israeli demand of collecting illegal arms from the
Palestinians which Israel raised during the meeting, Erekat said "
the Palestinian side is ready to carry out the agreements on
condition that Israel should meet its commitments."
</P>
<P>
Referring to a statement by Israeli Security Minister Shlumo Bin
Ami on formation of an international commission to compensate the
Palestinian refugees, Erekat said, "it is unacceptable by the
Palestinians and goes against international laws including U.N.
Security Council Resolution 194 which confirms the right of return
and compensation for Palestinian refuges." 
</P>
</TEXT>
