<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Industrial Investment in Bangladesh Surpasses 1 Bln U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 25 (Xinhua ) -- The number of registered industrial
projects in Bangladesh stood at 6,115 during the past four years
with estimated investment of 11.52 billion U.S. dollars, an
official statement published in the New Nation said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total registered investments, foreign investment amounts
to 7.32 billion dollars in 554 projects, according to the
statement of the Board of Investment.
</P>
<P>
Average registered investments during the four-year rule of the
present government are 145 per cent higher than previous
government's five-year (1991-96) tenure. The local investment has
increased 95 per cent while foreign investment 180 per cent.
</P>
<P>
The number of projects registered with the board in 10 years
from 1980 to 1990 was 31,872 with estimated investments of 4.38
billion dollars. It rose to 17.31 billion dollars in nine years
thereafter.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the implementation of the registered
projects is 80 per cent while the implementation of the foreign
projects is 50 per cent, which is satisfactory compared to other
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
"Investment scenario in the country has been brightening
gradually and it would accelerate with the improvement of
infrastructures like traffic links, port facilities and power and
telecommunications systems," the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
