<HEADLINE> China, Croatia Win Last Two Berths for Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympic silver medallists
China claimed their fifth straight place in the Olympics and
Croatia their first-ever one on the last day of the women's
volleyball final qualifying round on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
China, gold medallists in the 1984 Olympic Games, breezed past
Argentina 25-17, 25-11, 25-17, while Croatia defeated Italy 19-25,
25-22, 25-21, 25-22 in the eight-nation round robin, which is also
the Asian qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
Italy, who also qualified for the Olympics for the first time,
finished top with a 6-1 win-loss record to take the first spot for
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, China and Croatia ended with 5-2 records, with the
South Koreans taking second place as Asian qualifiers and China
and Croatia taking the final two.
</P>
<P>
South Korea sent Japan into sixth place with a 21-25, 25-12, 25-
18, 25-23 win, while the Netherlands were fifth, beating winless
Canada 25-17, 25-20, 26-24.
</P>
<P>
The four countries will join the top three World Cup finishers
Cuba, Russia, Brazil and continental winners Germany, the United
States, Peru and Kenya as well as hosts Australia in the Olympics.
</P>
</TEXT>
