<HEADLINE> Kenyans Shine in Gold Coast Marathon Races </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Kenyans Joseph Kahuga and Cosmas
Ndeti beat a field of Australian, New Zealand and Japanese men to
win the Gold Coast marathon and half-marathon in Australia on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kahuga covered the 42.195 kilometers marathon course along the
coast's beaches and broadwater in a time of two hours 16 minutes
38 seconds, well outside his best time of 2:07.59, to win the race.
</P>
<P>
Three-time Boston Marathon winner Ndeti won the half-marathon
race in 1:03.30.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan earned 20,000 Australian dollars (11,800 U.S.
dollars) for the first place finish plus a further 7,500
Australian dollars (4,425 U.S. dollars) in bonuses for leading at
the 30km, 35km and 40km marks.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's Phil Costley finished second in 2:16.42 and
Australian Magnus Michelsson was third in 2:17.34.
</P>
<P>
Local runner Samantha Hughes won the women's marathon in 2:42:
16, while the women's half-marathon was won by Takako Kotorida of
Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
