<HEADLINE> China Invests More in Science and Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China spent more on science and
education in the January-April period, according to the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the bureau showed the aggregate investment in
scientific research and polytechnic services in the first four
months this year reached 1.28 billion yuan (about 154.7 million U.
S. dollars), surging 21.4 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, investment in education, culture, health care,
broadcasting and social welfare amounted to 14.74 billion yuan (
about 1.8 billion U.S. dollars), up 17.3 percent over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has placed the development of science
and education high on its agenda in an effort to accelerate the
country's modernization process.  
</P>
</TEXT>
