<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Investment Up in First Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Total investment in China hit 361.
12 billion yuan (about 43.6 billion U.S. dollars) in the first
four months this year, a year-on-year increase of 9.3 percent,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The figure has not included investment by collectives and
individuals in both urban and rural areas. Of the total, 199.25
billion yuan (about 24 billion U.S. dollars) went to capital
construction projects, growing 4.7 percent, and 64.40 billion yuan
(about 7.8 billion U.S. dollars) was used for technical upgrades,
surging 15.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
In terms of regions, Guangdong Province, an economic
powerhouse in south China, had the largest amount of investment of
50.9 billion yuan (about 6.1 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Gansu Province enjoyed the fastest increase
among all provinces and autonomous regions, with its investment
soaring 51.8 percent to 2.64 billion yuan (about 319 million U.S.
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
