<HEADLINE> Sewerage Tunnel Collapse Kills Two in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRNA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were killed and
another missing on Saturday night when a sewerage tunnel collapsed,
the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of two victims, both young engineers, were found and
efforts are under way to recover the third one buried under the mud
in the vicinity of Tehran's main square of Vali-e Asr.
</P>
<P>
A technician for the emergency affairs told the agency that the
two victims had been suffocated.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when two engineers and another Afghan
worker of the contractual company stationed there for drilling.
</P>
<P>
An expert from the company, speaking on condition of anonymity,
blamed the district municipality for the incident.
</P>
<P>
However, the district mayor declined to comment on the causes
behind this tragic incident.
</P>
<P>
An officer in charge of the local fire department said that it
was a very hard task to recover the bodies since they were hidden
under a huge volume of soil.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of this incident, the district road was closed which
has caused a heavy traffic, IRNA added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
