<HEADLINE> Thai's Veeraphol Retains WBC Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Veeraphol Nakonluang of Thailand
retained his World Boxing Council bantamweight title with a
unanimous 12-round decision over challenger Toshiaki Nishioka of
Japan in Takasago, Japan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was the 31-year-old Veeraphol's fourth defense of the title
he won from Joichiro Tatsuyoshi of Japan in December 1998.
</P>
<P>
Both Gale Van Hoy and Dalby Shirley scored it 116-112 while
Martin Denkin made it 115-113, all in favor of Veeraphol. All
three judges are American.
</P>
<P>
It was Veeraphol's 27th victory, including 19 knockouts,
against one defeat. Nishioka has a record of 20 victories,
including 12 knockouts, against three defeats and one draw.
</P>
