<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Airport Records All-Time Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) - Passenger and air cargo figures
have set new 12-month records at Hong Kong International Airport (
HKIA).
</P>
<P>
Records were again set in the 12 months from June 1999 to May
this year, with more than 31.6 million passengers and 2.11 million
tons of airfreight passing through the airport. These records
follow directly the 12-month records set in April of 31.3 million
passengers and 2.09 million tons of cargo.
</P>
<P>
The records are markedly higher than the calendar year records
of 30.8 million passengers in 1996 and 1.9 million tons of cargo
in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
