<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sees Rise in Service Sector Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Total investment in the tertiary industry amounted to 224.10
billion yuan (about 27 billion U.S. dollars) between January and
April, jumping 9.6 percent year on year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in real estate, public services and consulting
services surged 18.6 percent to 112.56 billion yuan (about 13.6
billion U.S. dollars) over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some 6.36 billion yuan (about 768 million U.S.
dollars) was channeled into commerce, food services, material
supply and marketing, and storage, down 5.2 percent on an annual
basis.
</P>
<P>
In the banking and insurance sector, total investment stood at
1.57 billion yuan (about 190 million U.S. dollars), 5.6 percent
less than the same period of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
