<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Southern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake measuring
5.8 on the open-ended Richter scale jolted the southern part of
Japan's southernmost main island of Kyushu on Sunday afternoon,
the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage caused
by the quake.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, which occurred at around 3:34 p.m. (local time),
was felt in Miyazaki Prefecture and Kagoshima Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was estimated to be about 10
kilometers below the seabed near Tanegashima Island in Kagoshima
Prefecture, the agency said. 
