<HEADLINE> China's Output of Chemicals Grows Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry
maintained its growing momentum with the output of most major
products on the rise in the first four months this year, according
to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The production of chemical fertilizers climbed 4.6 percent on
an annual basis to 10.94 million tons, and that of chemical
pesticides grew by 1.8 percent to 236,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
During the period, 2.08 million tons of chemical fiber were
produced, up 14.8 percent year on year, while 3.12 million tons of
plastic products were turned out, up 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of ethylene surged 12.5 percent on an annual basis
to 1.61 million tons and that of plastic resin and polymers jumped
23 percent to 3.44 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The production of caustic soda grew by 16.8 percent to 2.15
million tons, and that of sulfuric acid went up 5.6 percent to 7.
29 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
