<HEADLINE> China Produces More Household Electrical Appliances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China's production of most
household electrical appliances grew steadily in the first four
months this year, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of household refrigerators jumped 14 percent year on
year to 4.37 million, and that of color TV sets increased by 5.2
percent to 13.9 million.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 5.49 million air conditioners in the
January-April period, up 18.9 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the output of household washing machines
climbed 11.8 percent to 5.19 million, and that of video recorders
surged 14.9 percent to 1.70 million.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to stimulate domestic demand. Its anti-
smuggling drive has also promoted sales of China-made household
electric appliances.  
</P>
