<HEADLINE> Guangdong Leads China in Industrial Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, an economic
powerhouse in south China, led the country in terms of industrial
added value between January and April this year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures from the bureau show that Guangdong's
industrial added value in the four months stood at 88.87 billion
yuan (about 10.7 billion U.S. dollars), surging 14.6 percent over
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The province was followed by east China's Jiangsu Province,
which reported an industrial added value of 76.40 billion yuan,
and Shandong Province, 74.68 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The national total for the period amounted to 694.10 billion
yuan, up 10.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
A pioneer in China's reform and opening up drive, Guangdong has
developed a full-blown processing industry and a large proportion
of its enterprises are export-oriented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
