<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Residents Having Highest Income in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- People in the south China city of
Shenzhen, China's first special economic zone, continued to enjoy
the highest income among the 35 major Chinese cities in April,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the bureau show that in April, residents
in Shenzhen had a per-capita monthly income of 1,669.63 yuan, and
a per-capita monthly disposable income of 1,653.06 yuan, with
their per-capita monthly living expenditure standing at 2245.75
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city was followed by Guangzhou and Shanghai in terms of
monthly per-capita income and disposable income. The per-capita
monthly income in Guangzhou was 1,055.46 yuan and that of Shanghai
900.17 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The average per-capita monthly income of 35 major Chinese
cities stood at 650.89 yuan, with a per-capita monthly disposable
income of 646.27 yuan and a per-capita monthly living expenditure
of 541.46 yuan. 
</P>
