<HEADLINE> China Win Olympic Berth at Women's Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympic silver medalists
China clinched their spot at the Sydney Games Sunday when they
beat Argentina to guarantee a place in the top four at the women's
volleyball final qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women, who earlier lost to Italy and the
Netherlands, stormed past the Argentines 25-17, 25-11, 25-17.
</P>
<P>
With five wins against two defeats, China joined Italy and
South Korea to enter the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
"It was really a difficult tournament," said Chinese coach Hu
Jin.
</P>
<P>
It will be China's fifth straight ticket to the Olympics since
the 1984 Los Angeles Games, where they won the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
The remaining available qualification spot would be decided by
the outcome of Croatia's match against Italy later in the day. A
defeat for the Croatians would leave Japan with a mathematical
possibility of qualifying if they win their game against South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The qualifiers from the tournament here will join the World Cup
's top three - Cuba, Russia, Brazil and continental winners
Germany, United States, Peru and Kenya as well as hosts Australia
in the Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
