<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Information Equipment Industry Grows Fast in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China's information equipment
industry grew fast in the first four months of 2000, according to
the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of program-controlled switchboards surged 26.4
percent year-on-year to 15.12 million lines in the January-April
period.
</P>
<P>
The production of optical communications equipment increased by
16.3 percent to 7,061 units, and that of carrier communications
equipment grew 11.3 percent to 3,043 units.
</P>
<P>
In the four months, the output of computers registered a surge
of 38.0 percent to 995 units while that of micro-computers soared
88.6 percent to 2.16 million.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, China produced 1.71 billion semiconductor
integrated circuits, jumping 60.1 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The production of mobile communications equipment fell a year-
on-year 34.2 percent to 1.33 million sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
