<HEADLINE> Shanxi, Top Coal Producer in China in Jan-Apr </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China turned out 254.006 million
tons of coal in the first four months this year, with north China'
s Shanxi Province registering the greatest coal output of 57.189
million tons, according to the latest figures from the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The province yielded 17.02 million tons of coal in April alone,
with the national total standing at 70.441 million, the bureau
said.
</P>
<P>
Following Shanxi are Shandong and Henan provinces in the
January-April period, with output standing at 26.085 million tons
and 22.769 million tons respectively. 
</P>
