<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5,000 MILF Rebels Killed Since April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Moro Islamic Liberation Front(
MILF) has lost 5,000 men, or one third of its force, as a result
of fierce fighting with government troops since late April, The
Manila Post reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, which used to have 15,000 fighters, now has at most
10,000 men left, and most of them have taken refuge in Camp
Abubakar, the MILF's headquarters, the paper said, quoting
military sources.
</P>
<P>
Government troops, which began launching offensives against
MILF encampments in the southern province of Maguindanao late
April, claimed they have captured more than 30 rebel camps and
expected to complete military operations soon in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The MILF rebels continue to hold to half a dozen satellite
bases around Camp Abubakar, but they are experiencing a shortage
of ammunition, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, police seized some 2,000 bullets, believed to be
destined for Camp Abubakar, at the North Harbor in Tondo, Manila.
</P>
<P>
President Joseph Estrada has warned that unless the peace talks
reach a positive conclusion by June, the entire might of the armed
forces would be unleashed on the MILF, which has been fighting for
two decades for an independent Islamic state in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The president also set three conditions on the extension of the
deadline to July 29 as requested by the MILF. The MILF was asked
to drop its bid for an independent state in exchange for expanded
autonomy, stop terroristic activities and lay down its arms.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
