<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Powerlifter Breaks World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Despite a wrist injury, Sutrisno
of Indonesia's Lampung province, managed to break the world record
in the bench event at the 15th National Games (PON) powerlifting
event in Surabaya, East Java, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sutrisno, 27, competing in the men's 60 kilograms division,
earned a gold medal after lifting a total of 675 kgs in the squat,
bench press and dead lift.
</P>
<P>
According to the Jakarta Post Sunday, Sutrisno lifted 186.5 kgs
in the bench press, beating the previous Asian record of 185.5 kgs
and the former world record of 186 kgs both set by Isagawa
Hiroyoki of Japan.
</P>
<P>
He also bettered the PON record of 160 kgs and national record
of 170 kgs, both held by himself.
</P>
<P>
Sutrisno expressed pride at his success as he considers PON a
very important sporting event for him. However, he was
dissatisfied with his total lift as he usually lifts 725 kgs
during training sessions.
</P>
<P>
He had malaria two weeks prior to PON and was still dealing
with a wrist injury which made him unable to lift anything heavier.
</P>
</TEXT>
