<HEADLINE> Chongqing Police Arrest Drug Dealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The police in this southwest
China metropolis arrested earlier this month four suspected drug
dealers and confiscated more than 50 kg of heroin.
</P>
<P>
The case is said to be the largest involving drug trafficking
that has ever occurred in the city since the People's Republic of
China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The police also seized 129,000 yuan (about 15,650 U.S. dollars)
in drug funds and two vehicles used to transport drugs.
</P>
<P>
The drug dealers confessed that they had bought the heroin from
a citizen of Myanmar in early June and sold drugs mixed with
coffee in Chongqing. 
</P>
