<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Land-use Principles for Western Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Land and
Resources has formulated the guiding principles for land-use
evaluation and approval in the 10 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities in western China.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry's Outline on Land Resources
Development and Use for West Development Program, major
infrastructure projects will be given top priority in land-use
evaluation and approval.
</P>
<P>
They include trunk lines of national expressways or trunk
highways linking towns and cities, selected town development
projects, airports, interprovincial railway projects, natural gas
pipeline projects and power plants.
</P>
<P>
Priority will also be given to application for land use for
urban infrastructure projects, new water conservancy projects
approved by the central government, selected mineral resources
development projects, and projects encouraged by the State
industrial polices.
</P>
<P>
Land use approval will not be given to projects which are
discouraged by the State industrial policies, such as those which
are technologically-backward, consume excess resources, and are
heavy polluters, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
It calls for policies to be formulated on land use for projects
geared to woo domestic and overseas investors to set up factories,
develop natural resources and provide technological upgrading for
existing enterprises in the western region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
