<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIBET: An international symposium on Tibetan medicine will be
held on July 15-17 in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous
Region. The event will be the first of this kind ever held in the
homeland of the 1,300-year-old unique system of medical research,
clinical practice and drug use.
</P>
<P>
WUHAN: A passenger aircraft of Wuhan Airlines crashed in
central China's Hubei Province on June 22, killing all 42 on board
including four crew members and 38 passengers.
</P>
<P>
HUNAN: The fourth model of a China-made unmanned car has
recently passed a road test in Changsha, capital of Hunan Province.
The car can perform all the normal functions that a driver could
do such as starting the ignition, changing gears and parking. The
car is capable of running at the maximum speed of 75.6 km/h.
Development of the first model of the car started in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
JIANGXI: The Nanchang Economic Development Zone has been
upgraded into a state-level economic zone. This is the first
national economic zone in this capital of east China's Jiangxi
Province. Opened in 1992, the Nanchang Economic Development Zone
has a complete set of infrastructure facilities, with investors
enjoying preferential policies.
</P>
<P>
ANHUI: Hefei, capital of east Anhui Province near Shanghai,
plans to become a modern metropolis in 10 years. The city is
expected to become an important educational base and a major
communications hub of the country, and a key industrial base in
the Yangtze River valley.
</P>
