<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese capital's largest resort, Beijing Green Resort,
opened Sunday in suburban Shunyi district. The new facility has
200 hectares of forest, more than 130 hectares of water and 33
hectares of beaches. Beijing now has a total of 15 forest parks,
which received some two million visitors in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Government opened a hotline on June 20
for citizens to air their complaints about city services. The new
service line, numbered 12345, operates with the most advanced
computer and telecommunication equipment. It has ten operators and
50 automatic service lines, all available for round-the-clock
calls.
</P>
<P>
China's Ministry of Information Industry launched a national
association for electronic commerce in Beijing on June 21. The
China Electronic Commerce Association will promote the development
of e-commerce via research and investigation, consulting, training
and exhibition.
</P>
<P>
