Organization (UNESCO) issued in Beijing on June 22 World Heritage
Certificates to four Chinese sites -- Wuyi Mountain in Fujian
Province, Dazu Stone Carvings in Chongqing, the Summer Palace and
the Temple of Heaven in Beijing. They were listed as world
heritage sites by UNESCO in 1998 and 1999.
</P>
