<P>
"Spring Bud 2000" Program Begins
</P>
<P>
The "Spring Bud 2000" Program, a national campaign to help
female school dropouts in poor areas, started June 17 in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The program has helped over 900,000 female students continue
their studies since it was launched in 1989.
</P>
<P>
An official with the China Children and Teenagers Fund said the
program has collected over 300 million yuan (about 36 million U.S.
dollars) in the past decade.
</P>
<P>
