<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Banks Operate Well in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Eight overseas banks approved to
do business in Chinese currency in Shenzhen lent out two billion
yuan in loans and raked in 29 million yuan in interest earnings in
the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
Information from the local taxation administration said the
overseas banks turned in 2.8 million yuan in taxes for business
operations in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Granting foreign banks with the right to do business in Chinese
currency yuan is an important step in opening up the financial
sector in China.
</P>
<P>
This has helped improve the confidence of foreign banks in
investing in Shenzhen and attracting more overseas banks to the
special economic zone. Some 20 overseas banks have built branch
organizations in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The capital needed by overseas banks in Shenzhen mainly comes
from inter-bank loans, as the eight overseas banks have all signed
medium- and long-term yuan loan agreements with local Chinese
banks.
</P>
<P>
The overseas banks then lend the Chinese currency loans to
overseas-financed ventures in Shenzhen, a regional financial
center in south China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Medical News: Weekly Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The following is a roundup of
China's medical news for the past week:
</P>
<P>
Listed Company to Move into Medicine
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Industrial United Holdings Co., Ltd. announced a plan
to place 50 million shares in a move to diversify from its core
business in wool and cotton fabrics to herbal medicine.
</P>
<P>
The company said it expected to net between 714 million and 868
million yuan through the share placement. United Holdings will use
about 450 million yuan from the receipts of the placement to
develop two herbal medicine subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
"China's traditional medicine is getting a foothold in the
global market," said analyst Cong Song of China Securities. "It is
wise for United Holdings to develop herbal medicine."
</P>
<P>
After the placement, United Holdings will have three main
businesses: textiles, medicine and e-commerce, and expects to
increase its profits to 94.6 million yuan this year, said Lu Shen,
president of the company.
</P>
<P>
China to Host First Pharmaceuticals Industry Exposition
</P>
<P>
China's first China's pharmaceuticals industry exposition,
China Pharmaceuticals Exposition 2000, will be held at the Beijing
International Exhibition Center September 12-15.
</P>
<P>
The China Pharmaceutical Industry Corp. and the China
International Trade Center Co., Ltd., co-organizers of the
exposition, announced that the items on display will include
chemical products, packaging machinery and materials, medicine-
making equipment and accessories, laboratory instruments,
equipment for quality testing, sanitary materials, and medical
books and journals.
</P>
<P>
Expected to attract much attention will be facilities for
pharmaceuticals enterprises to conduct technical renovation in
accordance with the GMP (Good Manufacturing Practice) standards,
as well as packaging materials and Internet-based medical service
products, according to the organizers.
</P>
<P>
Beijing to Host International Symposium on Stomatology
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Stomatology Association and Federation Dental
International will co-sponsor a symposium on stomatology in
Beijing September 17-19, with about 600 participants from both at
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The annual meeting will mainly focus on dentistry in the 21st
century, the latest developments in orthognathia surgery and
periodontal disease research, future orthodontic surgery, Chinese
traditional medicine and stomatology, new repair materials and new
concepts in clinical repair, management of dental clinics;
treatment of snoring and obstructive sleep apnea syndrome by using
oral prosthetic devices and treatment of cleft palates.
</P>
<P>
Morgan Stanley Invests in Chinese Pharmaceuticals Industry
</P>
<P>
Morgan Stanley, the world's largest investment bank, together
with some Chinese and other foreign investors, will put more than
100 million yuan (about 12.1 million U.S. dollars) and assets
worth 50 million yuan into a Chinese medicine producer.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Taiyang Pharmaceuticals Co., Ltd. has signed an
investment agreement with the China International Capital Co., Ltd.
, a Sino-foreign investment bank set up in 1995 by Morgan Stanley,
China Construction Bank and a Singapore investment company.
</P>
<P>
With the investment, the net assets of the company are expected
to surpass 250 million yuan, and its annual sales income will
reach 140 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
