<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal, Italy Enter Semis at Euro 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BURSSELS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Portugal beat Turkey and Italy
Downed Romania and both winners advanced to the semifinals after
their identical 2-0 victories in Saturday's quarter finals the
2000 European championships.
</P>
<P>
For Turkey and Romania, hitting at an opponent and blatant
theatrics to fool the referee turned into red cards and into
inglorious exits from Euro 2000.
</P>
<P>
Italy will face the winner of Sunday's quarter-final between
France and Spain while Italy will take on the winner of another
quarter-final between the Netherlands and Yugoslavia, also on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Two goals from Nuno Gomes capped a display of Latin flair with
more than a touch of samba soccer to it, as mastermind Luis Figo
steered his team 2-0 past Turkey, which already was in unchartered
territory by just making it into the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
A steely defense gave Italy the solid base and opportunistic
goals from Francesco Totti and Filippo Inzaghi brought the team
over Turkey earlier in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Gheorghe Hagi ended his long international career on
a shameful note, first committing a vile foul before the worst
kind of theatrics to fool the referee into giving a penalty. It
cost him a red card and he walked out of international soccer in
disgrace.
</P>
<P>
But if one color stood out, it was the claret-and-green of Luis
Figo and his men.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's golden boys were able to ride the class of their
Barcelona midfielder again and Nuno Gomes is riding the crest of a
scoring wave, slotting three goals in the three games he started
so far. He hadn't found the net in 12 earlier appearances.
</P>
<P>
Missing two more easy chances, he was still trying to score a
hat-trick when coach Humberto Coelho pulled him off in the 74th
minute.
</P>
<P>
"I'm disappointed not to have the chance to go for a hat-trick,
" Gomes said. "But I'm happy that we won."
</P>
<P>
So for the first time since 1984 Portugal is in the semifinal
of a major tournament again. That year it lost in an epic European
Championship match against France.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese creativity finally broke down Turkey's defensive
wall in the dying moments of the first half when Figo, quickly
turning into the star of the tournament, whipped the umpteenth
cross in front of goal and striker Nuno Gomes tecber.
</P>
<P>
In the 56 minute, when Turkey was already groggy from wave
after wave of Portuguese attacks, Figo faked his way past Hakan
Unsal, put a precision pass on the foot of the unmarked Nuno Gomes,
who only had to tap into the empty net to scored his third goal of
the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the match, Portugal confirmed its reputation as a
limitless well of creative talent,
</P>
<P>
"We never lost our heads. Everybody has their feet firmly on
the ground," said midfielder Costinha.
</P>
<P>
Turkey had been down a man since the 29th minute when Alpay
Ozalan was sent off for hitting Fernando Couto when both were down
after a duel for the ball in the air.
</P>
<P>
"When you play against a team like Portugal with 10 men it's
always going to be difficult," said Turkey's England-based Muzzy
Izzet.
</P>
<P>
"The sending off was a turning point," he said.
</P>
<P>
Dino Zoff's Italian team, hardly rated as title contenders
before the tournament, has now won four championship games in a
row. The coach though, was only "moderately satisfied" with his
team's performance, and disappointed with their play after Hagi
was expelled. "Some thought reaching the quarterfinals was
impossible, and we're happy with what we've accomplished," Zoff
said. "But we have to play much better. " 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000625.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
