<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Halard-Decugis Wins at Eastbourne Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 24 (Xinhua)-- Sixth-seed Julie Halard-Decugis of
France played some outstanding grass court tennis to beat Belgian
Dominique Van Roost 7-5 (7-4), 6-4 in a tough final to win the
women's tournament at Eastbourne, England, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The match was severely interrupted by rain but Halard-Decugis
kept her concentration to beat the rival.
</P>
<P>
In fact only 13 minutes of play were possible in the final
before black clouds and heavy rain prompted a delay on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchwoman had already broken fifth-seeded Van Roost's
serve and led 2-1 when play was suspended.
</P>
<P>
The match had already began 35 minutes late due to the weather -
but worse was to follow and the players were forced to wait for
three hours before a resumption was possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
