<HEADLINE> Ferrero Pulls Out of Wimbledon Tennis due to Back Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Juan Carlos Ferrero, who
threatened to boycott Wimbledon because of the seeding system, has
withdrawn because of a lower back injury, according to a Reuters
report.
</P>
<P>
His place in the draw was taken by lucky loser Wayne Black of
Zimbabwe. Black plays world number 13 Ferrero's original opponent
Karol Kucera of Slovakia on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ferrero and compatriots Albert Costa and Alex Corretja, all
clay court specialists, had written to the ATP Tour complaining
that the All England Club had ignored their world rankings and
excluded them from the Wimbledon seedings.
</P>
<P>
The three asked for a new draw and threatened to pull out of
the championships.
</P>
<P>
World number 15 Costa is scheduled to play 11th-seeded Dutchman
Richard Krajicek and world number 11 Corretja faces fellow
Spaniard Alberto Martin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
