<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2000GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat on Sunday stressed the need for Israel to carry out
the third phase of troop withdrawal from the West Bank, the
Egyptian information minister said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak and Arafat termed as "important" for Israel to go ahead
with the pullout, which was to have taken place on Friday, Safwat
el-Sherif told reporters after a meeting between the two leaders.
</P>
<P>
Israel has put off the troop withdrawal till July 7 as agreed by
the Palestinians. (Egypt-Mubarak-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli Cabinet approved Prime Minister Ehud
Barak's nomination of Center Party leader Amnon Lipkin-Shahak as
Transportation Minister on Sunday, leaving his post of Minister of
Tourism vacant.
</P>
<P>
The former chief of staff also automatically becomes a permanent
member of the prime minister's security cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Lipkin-Shahak is replacing Yitzhak Mordechai who resigned
following an indictment on sexual assault charges against him.
Lipkin-Shahak took over Mordechai's position as head of the Center
Party a month ago. (Israel-Portfolio)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Sunday
Israel is still open to peace talks with Syria, but its policy on
the sovereignty of the northeast bank of Lake Kinneret isnot
changed.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at Sunday morning's weekly cabinet meeting, Barak
reiterated the extent of Israeli withdrawal from the strategic
Golan Heights, which Israel occupied during the 1967 Middle East
War, depends on security arrangement between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Anyway, he added, the northeast shore of Lake Kinneret will
remain under Israeli control, according to a statement issued by
Barak's office after the meeting. (Israel-Syria-Kinneret)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on Sunday noted that
the coming weeks would be decisive and serious as the Palestinian
statehood would be declared by the end of them, said a report
reaching here from the West Bank City of Nablus.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who made a speech at the Kamal Gunblat School playground
in Nablus, said,"Decisive and the most serious weeks are ahead of
us, because the independent Palestinian state will be declared by
the end of them."
</P>
<P>
Palestinian and Israeli negotiating teams set September 13 for
reaching a final agreement on the future of Palestinian
territories.
</P>
<P>
(Palestine-Arafat-Coming Weeks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- A special committee of Syrian parliament on Sunday
gave its blessings to the nomination of Bashar al-Assad for the
post of president to succeed his late father, President Hafez al-
Assad, who died on June 10.
</P>
<P>
According to the official SANA news agency, the 70-member
committee of the 250-seat People's Assembly discussed the
nomination of Bashar by the ruling Baath party and expressed its "
total support" for his candidacy for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
A full session of the parliament is expected to be held Monday
to approve Bashar's nomination and set a date for a referendum for
the country's nearly 7 million voters to decide whether Bashar will
be the new ruler. (Syria-Bashar) 
</P>
</TEXT>
